  "body": "\n### Description\n\n*Type*: Bug\n*Summary*: usually `Close` button just closes the current window, but doesn't close app (checked in Riot, Telegram, Slack), but in case of Status it stops whole application. It may cause the accidental closing of app, which is definitely annoying when you should each time to log in and enter a password.\n\n#### Expected behavior\nStatus is still opened in Dock (not stopped)\n\n#### Actual behavior\nStatus app is closed\n\n### Reproduction\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\n\n- Open Status\n- Log in\n- Click on red close button\n<img width=\"121\" alt=\"monosnap 2018-09-13 18-05-46\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/45504398-6f95da00-b792-11e8-9578-ec769bc31459.png\">\n\n\n### Additional Information\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n* Status version: nightly \n* Operating System: Mac Os X",
